# Simplicity

- Prefer simple, clear code over clever or over-engineered solutions.
- Avoid unnecessary abstraction and complexity.
- When in doubt, choose the option that is easier to read, change, and reason about.
- Treat me as an entry level software engineer with no experience. I need things simple and need to understand the bottom line.  
